version_description: Compatibility update for iOS 13

If you would like more information about payment types impacted by the Australian Government’s recent stimulus package you can visit https://www.servicesaustralia.gov.au/individuals/subjects/affected-coronavirus-covid-19/if-you-already-get-payment-from-us-coronavirus-covid-19

- Update to My Claims service

The service where customers can report their employment income has been updated with a new look and feel, and as well as English, is now also available in the following languages:
- Arabic
- Persian (Farsi)
- Chinese Simplified
- Vietnamese

If your device is set to one of the supported languages, the Report Employment Income service will display in this language.
·  UI improvements

- Minor enhancement to Update Address service
- Introduce navigation to Income and Asset management
·   Minor UI enhancements

- Ability for Youth Allowance recipients to record a Voiceprint for easy Identity confirmation when calling Centrelink
- Reminder notifications now available to Reporters on their reporting day

- New service for Paid Parental Leave recipients to help manage their Flexible Paid Parental Leave days
- Pre-filled employer details now available to some reporting customers through Single Touch Payroll
- Minor enhancements
- Minor bug fixes

- Changes for ParentsNext recipients when reporting income
- Update to the Advances (Make a Payment) service to help reduce repayment errors

- Additional reminder notifications

Report employment income - The way you report your employment income has changed. To accommodate this change:
- The service has been updated to incorporate the required changes
- A forced update has been applied to the reporting service to ensure you meet your new reporting obligations
